full_text:
1. Short rant on misunderstanding Soviet history, the Communist Party of China, and Xi Jinping in the Coronavirus handling.

I've seen a number of people comparing this to the Chernobyl incident, and how that exposed the USSR's maladministration.

This is a silly comparison.
description: Homo sacer / S Asia at @third_pole/ Opinions personal / Books: The Kingdom at the Centre of the World, Jimmy the Terrorist, others / Tzedek tzedek tirdof
full_retweet_text: No Value Mentioned

full_text:
3. China faces none of these challenges, or anything remotely comparable to them in combination.

In actual point of fact, much of the world is deeply invested in the success of China, the Chinese people even more so.

Like Big Finance, it is "too big to fail".
description: Homo sacer / S Asia at @third_pole/ Opinions personal / Books: The Kingdom at the Centre of the World, Jimmy the Terrorist, others / Tzedek tzedek tirdof
full_retweet_text: No Value Mentioned

full_text:
5. Secondly, the numbers might be huge, but they are still relatively small for China. Total confirmed dead are still less than 2,000.

Southeast Asia (with half the pop of China) had annual death rate of 6,000 from dengue from 2000-2010: https://t.co/4YbOUcUDq6
description: Homo sacer / S Asia at @third_pole/ Opinions personal / Books: The Kingdom at the Centre of the World, Jimmy the Terrorist, others / Tzedek tzedek tirdof
full_retweet_text: No Value Mentioned

full_text: 6. The Ebola virus outbreak of 2014 in Sierra Leone, a much smaller, much more open, and more vulnerable country, did not lead to a major impact on the regime, and President Koroma (despite many issues) served out his full term easily.
description: Homo sacer / S Asia at @third_pole/ Opinions personal / Books: The Kingdom at the Centre of the World, Jimmy the Terrorist, others / Tzedek tzedek tirdof
full_retweet_text: No Value Mentioned

full_text:
7. There is no credible reason to suggest that the Party will pay a high cost for the handling of the issue.

Frankly, given the very obvious anti-China being put out, the regime will likely wrap itself in hurt nationalism, and emerge stronger.
description: Homo sacer / S Asia at @third_pole/ Opinions personal / Books: The Kingdom at the Centre of the World, Jimmy the Terrorist, others / Tzedek tzedek tirdof
full_retweet_text: No Value Mentioned

full_text:
8. The most likely outcome is that people will note the problems, and say, "The Party could have handled it better, but given that nobody was helping, and everybody hates China, they didn't do a bad job."

Xi might even get rid of potential rivals (there are no serious ones).
description: Homo sacer / S Asia at @third_pole/ Opinions personal / Books: The Kingdom at the Centre of the World, Jimmy the Terrorist, others / Tzedek tzedek tirdof
full_retweet_text: No Value Mentioned

full_text:
9. All this hyperventilating about China, and Xi's, vulnerability, in the end, is setting up fantasies which have little basis in fact, and no correlation with the history of other such epidemics, or of China.

-end-
description: Homo sacer / S Asia at @third_pole/ Opinions personal / Books: The Kingdom at the Centre of the World, Jimmy the Terrorist, others / Tzedek tzedek tirdof
full_retweet_text: No Value Mentioned
